    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i know i should talk to them but my doctor is so dismissive of anything that isnt a pill. i've been reading online that garlic extract is actually a really potent natural anticoagulant and that if i just take a high enough dose i might not even need the warfarin anymore. if i started taking like 3000mg of garlic extract a day would that be enough to keep me safe from clots? i just want to avoid the side effects of the meds",
